<HEADLINE> Muslim Party Reveals Candidates for Bosnia Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic Action Party (SDA)
has submitted for the upcoming elections lists of candidates led
by members of the current presidency and the prime minister, the
ruling Muslim party said today.
</P>
<P>
Halid Genjac, head of the SDA election committee, said at a
press conference here that Bosnian President Alija Izetbegovic is
the leading candidate on the SDA list for the three-member
presidency of Bosnia-Herzegovina.
</P>
<P>
The SDA has submitted 4,960 candidates for elections at levels
of the republic, entities, cantons and municipalities. The
Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe has decided
elections for Bosnia to be held on September 14 and parties have
to submit their lists of candidates before 19:00 (local time)
today.
</P>
<P>
Ejup Ganic, a member of the Bosnian collective presidency and
vice-president of the Bosnian (Muslim-Croat) Federation, will head
the list for the assembly of Bosnia-Herzegovina, Genjac said.
</P>
<P>
Bosnian Prime Minister Hasan Muratovic will head the SDA list
for the assembly of the Bosnian Federation, the SDA official said.
</P>
<P>
Under the terms of the Dayton peace accord, Bosnia is formed by
two entities, the federation and Republika Srpska, which will be
linked by the presidency, assembly and government at the national
level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
