<HEADLINE> Lebanese Prime Minister Arrives in Paris </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Lebanese Prime Minister Rafic Al
Hariri arrived here today for a brief visit.
</P>
<P>
Soon after his arrival, Hariri went to the Presidential Palace
at the Elysee to hold talks with President Jacques Chirac on the
political situation in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
The Lebanese prime minister was in Paris twice earlier this
year to seek economic aid for the reconstruction of Lebanon and
political support after Israel launched the Grapes of Rage
offensive against Lebanon in April. 
