<HEADLINE> Zambia to Export Sawn Timber to S.Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Zambia will export sawn timber and
electricity transmission poles worth nearly one million U.S.
Dollars to South Africa, Botswana and Namibia within next six
months.
</P>
<P>
A total of 26,000 poles will be transported to those countries
in the latter half of the year.
</P>
<P>
Zambia is also in the process of exporting another consignment
of transmission poles to Tanzania, according to today's Times of
Zambia.
</P>
<P>
The Zambia Forest and Forestry Industries Corporation will
strive to capture the largest possible share of the local and
international markets by improving production and efficiency,
said the corporation managing director Charles Mwale in
northern Zambia on Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
