<HEADLINE> Kazibwe Appointed Vice-President of Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 4 (Xinhua)-- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
reappointed Specioza W. Kazibwe Vice-President of Uganda here
today.
</P>
<P>
The appointment was unanimously approved by the country's
new parliament today.
</P>
<P>
Kazibwe , 41, is a member of parliament for the
Chiguru-South constituency, Iganga District, about 100 km east
of Kampala.
</P>
<P>
A mother of five children, Kazibwe, was first appointed Deputy
Minister of Industry and Technology in 1991. She was later
appointed Minister of Gender and Community Development and in
November 1994 she was elevated to the vice-presidency in a
cabinet reshuttle. enditem

