<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 617 Die of Traffic Accidents in May in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Traffic accidents killed 617 people
in France in May this year, 45 fewer than those in the same month
last year, said Highway Security in a communique today.
</P>
<P>
For 10 months running, the number of casualties in traffic
accidents has been declining in France after the government
announced the lowering of the level of tolerance of alcohol in
blood to 0.5 grams per liter.
</P>
<P>
The Highway Security said that the number of people killed in
traffic accidents from June 1995 to May 1996 in France stood at
8,135, the lowest since 1956.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, the number of people who died in traffic accidents in
France totaled 8,412.
</P>
<P>
In May this year, the number of traffic accidents stood at
9,637, which was 1,903 fewer than that in May 1995. Altogether
13,165 people were injured in traffic accidents in May. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
