<HEADLINE> Urban Construction Should be Scientific, Li Ruihuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Senior Chinese official Li Ruihuan
today urged city planners to attach great importance to urban
development to ensure it stands the test of time.
</P>
<P>
Visiting an exhibition of the progress achieved in urban
construction, Li, chairman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Committee, said that economic growth in the past
decade and more has changed the appearance of many Chinese cities.
</P>
<P>
China's cities currently are investing heavily in urban
construction, which eventually will turn architectural blueprints
into reality.
</P>
<P>
"Yet urban development also faces challenges: if it is not
properly handled, the outlook of the city will be affected, thus
causing great losses," said Li, also a member of the Standing
Committee of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
He said that city officials should not change the city's plans
on a whim, because these guidelines are created by experts and
approved by the local people's congresses and the State Council.
</P>
<P>
If plans need to be changed, proper procedures should be
followed, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Leaders of cities should learn from the other countries their
useful experiences in urban construction, and not merely repeat
what the other countries have done," Li said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
