<HEADLINE> Jordanian-Yemeni Committee Ends Meeting in Amman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The Joint Jordanian-Yemeni Higher
Committee concluded its two-day meeting here today after signing
a minutes of the sessions and an agreement on cooperation in
electricity.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was co-chaired by Jordan's Prime Minister Abdul Karim
Kabariti and his Yemeni counterpart Abdul Aziz Abdul Ghani.
</P>
<P>
In an statement issued at the end of the meeting, Kabariti said
ties between the two countries are "deep and solid," stressing
Jordan supports Yemen's reconstruction efforts.
</P>
<P>
The Yemeni prime minister praised the cooperation between
Jordan and Yemen, saying that his country highly appreciates
Jordan's support of Yemen's reconstruction plans and its
stability.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also produced a political communique on
coordination of policies on various regional and international
issues with an emphasis on working jointly to enhance inter-Arab
relations. 
</P>
