<HEADLINE> Forum Discusses Development of Regional Telecom Networks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Telecommunications experts from
six Asian countries and several international organizations met
today for another round of talks on telecoms cooperation and
developing the sector in the Mekong subregion.
</P>
<P>
The agenda of the second Subregional Telecommunication Forum
(STCF) includes a discussion of the terms of reference for
preparation studies for several projects and the drawing up of a
work plan for the STCF.
</P>
<P>
Thirteen transmission projects and five studies were endorsed
by the first ministerial meeting in Manila last November to set up
optical fiber cable links between the six countries along the
Mekong River: China, Laos, Thailand, Vietnam, Myanmar and
Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of a subregional telecom network should lead
to an improvement in the availability and quality of the telecom
services of the six countries and help them catch up with the
international standards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
