<HEADLINE> US-Angolan Relations at Best Stage, Says US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- US Ambassador to Angola Donald
Steinberg said here today that the ties between the two
countries are now at "the best stage" since they established
diplomatic relations in l993.
</P>
<P>
He told a press conference that the establishment of
diplomatic relations between the two countries has opened doors
for their cooperation.
</P>
<P>
However, he added, the instability in the southern African
country has hindered the development of the friendly relations
between the United States and Angola in recent years.
</P>
<P>
There was a turn for the better last December when Angolan
President Eduardo dos Santos paid a visit to the United States
and held talks with US President Bill Clinton, he said.
</P>
<P>
The bilateral trade relations are good, he said, adding that
Angola is now the third largest trade partner and the second
largest investment country of the United States in the sub-Sahara
region. enditem

