<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Speaker of the National
Grand Assembly Mustafa Kalemli said here today that China is a
very important country in view of its geography, population
resources and economic development.
</P>
<P>
Kalemli made the remarks while meeting with He Luli, vice-mayor
of Beijing who is visiting Turkey.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting held in the parliament premises, he said
that Turkey and China would further develop their ties in the
economic, political, cultural and social fields as there is no
any political problems between the two countries.
</P>
