<HEADLINE> Chinese President Arrives in Kyrgyzstan on State Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BISHKEK, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
arrived here today on a two-day state visit to Kyrgyzstan, the
first visit to the central Asian republic by a Chinese head of
state.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement distributed at the airport, Jiang said
the main purpose of his visit to the "friendly neighbor" is to
explore ways to further develop friendly and good-neighborly
relations on a strategic basis into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
China and Kyrgyzstan are linked by common mountains and rivers,
and their friendly, good-neighborly, mutually-beneficial and
cooperative relationship has enjoyed sound and steady development
since 1992, when the two countries established diplomatic ties,
said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Jiang is expected to exchange views with Kyrgyz President Askar
Akayevich Akayev and other leaders of Kyrgyzstan on bilateral
relations and international issues of common concern as well as
signing a number of documents.
</P>
<P>
"It is my belief that this visit will help to deepen our mutual
understanding, trust and friendship, and bring friendly relations
and cooperation between China and Kyrgyzstan to a new level,"
Jiang stated.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president flew to Bishkek, the fifth leg of his
six-nation tour of Europe and central Asia, after successfully
winding up his state visit to Uzbekistan, which was preceded by
visits to Spain, Norway and Romania. 
</P>
</TEXT>
