<HEADLINE> UNITA Closes 4 More Quartering Camps in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Angola's former rebel movement
UNITA closed four more troops assembly camps early in the week in
northern and central provinces, indicating continued progress in
the peace process of the southern African country.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement released today by the United Nations
peace verification mission in Angola, out of the total 14 UNITA
quartering camps, eight have been closed, with 5844 of the entire
52350 UNITA soldiers demobilized from the camps.
</P>
<P>
The lately closed camps include those in Andula of the
central province of Bie, Quibala in Kwanz-Sul Province, Calata
of the northern province of Malange and Chicuma in the coastal
province of Benguela.
</P>
<P>
The UNITA has surrendered more than 26700 weapons, including
eight tanks and 68 pieces of artillery. 
</P>
