<TEXT>
<P>
BISHKEK, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin wound
up his two-day state visit to Kyrgyzstan and left here for Alma
Ata, Kazakhstan this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Before departure, Jiang said his visit has been fruitful in
promoting mutual trust and strengthening cooperation.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Jiang held talks with Kyrgyz President Askar
Akayev, Speaker of the Legislative Assembly Mukar Cholphonbayev,
Speaker of the Assembly of People's Representative Almanbet
Matubraimov and Prime Minister Apas Jumagulov.
</P>
<P>
The two sides signed a joint declaration, an agreement on
border demarcation and six cooperation documents.
</P>
<P>
Jiang is expected to arrive in Kazakhstan today for a three-day
state visit to the country at the invitation of President
Nursultan Nazarbayev. 
</P>
</TEXT>
