<HEADLINE> Chirac to Visit Middle East in Autumn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 4 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac will
pay a visit to Lebanon, Syria, the Palestinian automonous
territory of Gaza and Israel in late September and early October.
</P>
<P>
Chirac made the announcement after meeting with visiting
Lebanese Prime Minister Rafik Al Hariri.
</P>
<P>
The president also asked Foreign Minister Herve de Charette to
visit the Middle East in late July.
</P>
<P>
This will be the president's first visit to Syria, Israel and
Gaza. Chirac paid a visit to Lebanon in April.
</P>
<P>
On the situation in the Middle East after the forming of the
new Israeli government of Benjamin Netanyahu, Chirac said he would
wait to "produce a judgement on what policy will be pursued" by
the new Israeli government.
</P>
<P>
Chirac reaffirmed France's willingness to push forward the
Middle East peace process as has been defined in the agreements
signed in Oslo and Taba between Israel and its Arab neighbors.
</P>
<P>
He said that the European Union, the G-7 group and France share
most of the positions adopted by Arab countries at the Arab Summit
held in Cairo late last month. 
</P>
