<HEADLINE> UN Allocates Fund for Refugees Residing in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations High
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) has allocated 25 million
U.S. dollars for refugees residing in Iran, according to a U.N.
official here today.
</P>
<P>
UNHCR representative Peter Bertrand said 50 percent of the
money would be spent on repatriating Afghan refugees in Iran.
</P>
<P>
He appreciated Iranian contribution to building 50 schools and
refugee camps to provide accommodation and education for Afghan
and Iraqi refugees living in the country.
</P>
<P>
He said Iran has extended valuable health service and family
planning service to 5,000 women refugees living in refugee
townships.
</P>
<P>
Bertrand arrived at the Caspian town of Ramsar to attend a
seminar on studying the health and medical requirements of the
foreigners taking refuge in Iran.
</P>
<P>
According to a report, an Iranian official from the Interior
Ministry said annual U.N. aid for refugees in Iran was adequate
for only seven days of their current expenses.
</P>
<P>
The official said there were 2.5 million refugees in Iran, each
costing Iran two dollars per day.
</P>
<P>
He called on international organizations to increase their aid
to Iran for the refugees.
</P>
<P>
Refugees in Iran come mainly from neighboring Iraq and
Afghanistan, as well as Bangladesh and some other Asian
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
