<HEADLINE> Zaire Urges Repatriation of Rwandans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Zairean Deputy Prime Minister
Kititua Ntuoiansi today appealed for a speedy repatriation of
over one million Rwandan refugees in his country, calling the
refugee situation "explosive".
</P>
<P>
"It is simply beyond our capacity to manage them any more. We
are calling for their speedy repatriation," said Ntuoiansi in an
interview with Xinhua today.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier who doubles as Foreign Minister, is in the
Cameroonian capital of Yaounde to attend the ongoing Council of
Ministers meeting of the Organization of African Unity (OAU).
</P>
<P>
"They (meaning refugees) destroyed schools, villages and
towns, and caused lots of border trouble for our country. With
their presence, we even cannot hold smooth general elections," he
noted.
</P>
<P>
"We earnestly appeal for the OAU, United Nations High
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR), the international community to
take effective steps to relieve Zaire's refugees burden," said
Ntuoiansi.
</P>
<P>
Zaire, with its largest share of refugees burden in Africa,
now hosts 1.6 million African refugees in its territory,
including over one million Rwandans, mostly the majority Hutus
who fled for fear of revenge after the 1994 killings of up to a
million Tutsis and moderate Hutus at home. 
</P>
</TEXT>
