<HEADLINE> 13th Jerusalem Film Festival Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The 13th Jerusalem Film Festival
opened here this evening with more than 60 countries and regions
participating.
</P>
<P>
China has two feature films for the festival: On the Beat,
directed by Ning Ying; Temptress Moon, directed by Chen Kaige.
</P>
<P>
John Malkovich, star of silver screen, stage performer and
director, opened the festival. Malkovich is best known for his
performances in Dangerous Liaisons, Of Mice and Men, The
Killing Fields, and many other films.
</P>
<P>
The gala evening was held in the historic Sultan's Pool
Amphitheatre, with an audience of 5,000, a display of fireworks,
cocktail party plus the outdoor viewing of Robert Alman's
large-screen Kansas City.
</P>
<P>
Awards and prizes include the Wolgin Awards for Israeli
Cinema for best feature film, best documentary and best short
subjects; Lipper Award for Best Israeli Screenplay and the Wim
van Leer Award for High School Students.
</P>
<P>
International prizes at the 13th Jerusalem Film Festival are
Wim Van Leer in Spirit of Freedom. Films in competition
include: Bombay (India), At Full Gallop (Poland), Haifa
(Palestine/Netherlands), O Judeo (Brazil), Nothing Personal (Ireland),
Too Late (Romania), Shtetl (USA), and three films from Israel.
</P>
<P>
The second international prize for Mediterranean Cinema
includes: L'amore Molesto (Italy), A Propose de Nice (France), A
Summer In La Goulette (Tunisia), Flamenco (Spain), Haifa
(Palestine), Premeditated Murder (Serbia), and others.
</P>
<P>
The festival will last until July 13. 
</P>
</TEXT>
