<HEADLINE> PKK Rebels Attack Military Vehicle in Eastern </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The Kurdish Worker's Party (PKK)
rebels today attacked a military vehicle of the Turkish security
forces, who escorted two Turkish reporters, in Tunceli province,
eastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Anatolia News Agency reported this evening that a group of PKK
rebels fired at the military vehicle with rockets on the
Tunceli-Elazig Highway at 16:30 local time, but caused no
casualty. The vehicle was carrying two Star TV reporters and some
soldiers of the security forces.
</P>
<P>
The report said that soon after the incident, the Turkish
security forces launched an operation in search of the PKK rebels
who attacked the military vehicle. Two PKK rebels were killed
during the operation, the report added.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has continuously attacked the military targets in
southeastern Turkey in recent days and the Turkish security
forces have staged large-scale operations in pursuit of the PKK
rebels both in southeastern Turkey and in northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
More than 20,000 people, including PKK rebels, civilians and
government troops, have been killed in the armed conflicts since
the PKK started to fight for self-rule in southeast Turkey
in August 1984. 
</P>
</TEXT>
