<HEADLINE> Zambian Commercial Banks Meet Capital Requirement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Almost all Zambian commercial banks
have met the 1.25 billion Kwacha (one million US Dollars) capital
adequacy deadline set 18 months ago, Bank of Zambia announced
here today.
</P>
<P>
Public Relations Manager of the bank Kabinga Pande said some
of the commercial banks have already exceeded the two billion
Kwacha December requirement.
</P>
<P>
He said the Zambian Central Bank has told the banks which have
no sufficient capital to increase their capital or reduce their
assets.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his confidence that once all plans materialize
all the banks will be able to build up and maintain their capital
to the required levels.
</P>
<P>
Pande said that in addition every bank shall at all times
maintain total capital equivalent of less than 10 percent of its
total risk-weighted assets.
</P>
<P>
The capital adequacy regulations demand the commercial banks
have by the end of June 1.25 billion Kwacha and by the end of
this December two billion Kwacha. 
</P>
</TEXT>
