<HEADLINE> French Airliner Inaugurates Flight to Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 4 (Xinhua) -- A French international
airliner, CORSAIR, today inaugurated its direct flight services
from Paris, France to the Kilimanjaro International Airport (KIA)
in northern Tanzanian.
</P>
<P>
The French airliner, which operates to 54 destinations around
the world, made the maiden flight with its jumbo jet 300-747
Boeing, which landed at KIA at 7:50 a.m. this morning.
</P>
<P>
The flight with 591 passengers, out of which 100 were French
tourists, was accorded the warm welcome by hundreds of workers of
the KIA plus Tanganyika Wildlife Safari tour officials.
</P>
<P>
According to a report reaching here from Arusha, CORSAIR
General Manager Bernard Asacher told reporters at the airport
immediately after arrival that his airliner replaced Air France,
which stopped its services to KIA last April due to economic
problems.
</P>
<P>
Asacher said for a start CORSAIR would have one flight every
Thursday and plans are underway to increase its flight services
to the country by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
The CORSAIR chief said the flights would facilitate exports of
flowers to Europe and boost tourism in the country.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Minister for Natural Resources and Tourism Juma
Ngasongwa appealed to other international air lines to emulate
CORSAIR by establishing direct flights from Europe to KIA as
their gate way to tourist destination in Tanzania and elsewhere.
</P>
</TEXT>
