<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves $835 Million Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 4 (Xinhua) --The World Bank has recently
approved three loans totaling 835 million U.S. dollars for
projects in Russia and Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
Russia will receive 525 million dollar loans for its two
projects in coal sector, which includes a 500 million dollars for
its coal sector adjustment project and 25 million dollars for its
coal sector restructuring implementation assistance project. The
coal sector adjustment loan will be used to help the government
put in place a consistent policy and institutional framework for
the restructuring of the coal sector and provide assistance in
implementing the initial steps of the overall restructuring
program.
</P>
<P>
A 310 million dollar loan is earmarked for Ukraine's enterprise
development adjustment project. It will support the government's
trade and price liberalization, privatization, capital market
development, and post-privatization restructuring programs.
</P>
