<HEADLINE> Wild Elephants Driven Away from Western Nepali </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Villagers and army soldiers in
west Nepal have managed to drive away two wild elephants who had
played havoc with several villages in the Chitwan district in the
past three weeks, a report reaching here today said.
</P>
<P>
The two elephants, from the neighboring Chitwan National Park,
were driven away by using 19 domestic elephants provided by the
national park authorities, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The wild elephants had killed one villager and destroyed about
100 houses in the villages.
</P>
<P>
The Department of National Parks has decided to keep 10
domestic elephants at these affected villages to prevent the
possible comeback of the wild ones, it added. 
</P>
