<HEADLINE> Dial for Location of Your Brick </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- If you want to know where is the
engraved brick you paid to have put in Centennial Olympic Park,
please call.
</P>
<P>
The Olympic organizers have offered two telephone numbers that
you can dial to find out where to look when the park opens July 13.
</P>
<P>
You will need to provide the name of the person who placed the
order, the inscription on the brick or the number from the
certificate sent to confirm the brick order.
</P>
<P>
The 325,000 bricks are arranged around large granite slabs
engraved with numbers, and operators will look up the number your
brick is near.
</P>
<P>
In the park, five ATM-like kiosks with touch screens will
disperse the same information on small receipts imprinted with
park maps.
</P>
<P>
Bricks ordered by January 1 where installed in the park,
beginning in the central plaza area. Another 13,000 ordered after
that date will be put in the park after the Olympics. 
</P>
