<HEADLINE> Pakistan's Punjab Government to Spend Big Money </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The Government of Pakistan's
Punjab province will spend 2.725 billion rupees (77.8 million US
dollars) on education in the current fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The official Associated Press of Pakistan reported here today
that 262.7 million rupees (7.5 million dollars) will be spent on
secondary education, 204.1 million rupees (5.8 million dollars) on
college education, and 104.7 million rupees (2.9 million dollars)
on technical education in Punjab.
</P>
<P>
In various kinds of training sectors, about 1.872 billion
rupees (53.5 million dollars) will be allocated.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government also allocated 78 million rupees (2.2
million dollars) for all sort of scholarships.
</P>
<P>
The fiscal year 1996-97 began on July 1 and will end on June 30
next year.
</P>
<P>
Punjab, the most populous province in Pakistan, enjoys a higher
education standard than that of the other provinces.  
</P>
