<HEADLINE> Shanghai Pounded by Heavy Rain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 5 (Xinhua) -- China's largest city was pounded
by 18 hours of heavy rain, which flooded 30,000 houses and turned
most city streets into wading pools.
</P>
<P>
The downpour in Shanghai lasted from 8 p.m. Thursday until 2
p.m. today, with an average rainfall of 87.6 millimeters. In the
downtown Nanshi District, rain levels reached 141.4 millimeters.
</P>
<P>
No deaths or injuries were reported.
</P>
<P>
The Suzhouhe River, which runs through the city, has risen
above the danger level. Excessive rainfall also has affected the
growth of vegetables in outlying areas.
</P>
<P>
Rain has fallen on Shanghai since June 24; the total accumulation
is 270 millimeters.
</P>
<P>
Local weather forecasts predict rain will continue in Shanghai
for the next couple of days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
