<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Loan Shark Syndicate Smashed In HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong police today smashed a
loan shark syndicate that has been in operation for the last ten
years by exploiting money borrowers at a illegal interest rate.
</P>
<P>
Police officers arrested two men and two women in a spate of
raids today following a month-long investigation into the
syndicate.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the police said that there were over 200 debtors
getting involved in the syndicate over the past 18 months, and the
total amount of loans added up to three million HK dollars
(385,000 US dollars ).
</P>
<P>
The syndicate reportedly charged an interest rate over the
prescribed legal limit, withheld the debtors' bank passbooks and
bank cards as collateral security, and threatened debtors with
inflammatory words.
</P>
<P>
The four arrested, aged between 38 and 52, were accused of
several offenses against the Hong Kong Money Lenders Ordinance.
</P>
</TEXT>
