<HEADLINE> Measures Urged To Control Prices of Chemical Fertilizers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Immediate measures should be taken
to eliminate the chaos in the country's production and supply of
chemical fertilizer, a senior official said today.
</P>
<P>
Problems surrounding the country's fertilizer supply have
resulted in high prices that are causing farmers to complain, said
State Councilor Chen Junsheng during a tele-conference on the
country's major farm-use materials held in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
China had an adequate chemical fertilizer supply for this
year's spring planting, but Chinese farmers cannot afford the high
price of fertilizer, Chen said.
</P>
<P>
The adequate and cost-efficient supply of chemical fertilizer
is linked to the development of China's agriculture and the
stability of rural areas, Chen said.
</P>
<P>
He called on fertilizer producers and government administrators
to take firm measures that will guarantee the sufficient supply
and reasonable price of fertilizer.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that a chemical fertilizer reserve system be
established to control prices of chemical fertilizer, and that
tougher measures be taken to protect the interests of Chinese
farmers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
