<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Two persons died on the spot when
a electric transformer exploded at a village in West Nepal's
Baglung district, the official news agency RSS said today.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place Thursday night when a local power
station generated more electricity than the capacity of the
transformer, it said.
</P>
<P>
Three other villagers were injured in the explosion, it was
reported.
</P>
<P>
