<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The Ugandan parliament has
unanimously approved a request by President Yoweri Museveni to
increase cabinet ministers from 21 to 25 and support (deputy)
ministers from 21 to 36.
</P>
<P>
The request, which was made through Speaker James Wapakhabulo,
is intended to accommodate various people on ethnic and religious
grounds in the ministerial positions in the new government, local
reports said today.
</P>
<P>
