<HEADLINE> Floods Besiege Villages in Southern Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, July 5 (Xinhua)-- Floods are reported to have
besieged eight villages around Jowhar Town, 90 km north of here,
after the Shabelle River has crushed its banks.
</P>
<P>
The floods have also destroyed a number of houses in the
villages. More than 500 people there are currently being given
food by merchants using tractors.
</P>
<P>
The floods have also cut off the tarmac road linking
Mogadishu to Middle Shabelle Region.
</P>
<P>
According to the local authorities, the floods have also
destroyed 3,000 hectares of farmland, disappointing the good
havest that was expected during this season.
</P>
<P>
Middle Shabelle region is a producer of maize, sorghum, beans,
sesame and rice in the Horn of Africa country.
</P>
<P>
According to the European Union funded aid agencies operating
in Middle Shabelle Region, the floods have far gone beyond
control.
</P>
<P>
EU Speical Envoy to Somalia Sigurd Illing, who visited the
flood affected areas of the region yesterday, expressed concern
over the crop situation in the region this year. enditem


