<HEADLINE> OAU Observers Term Ugandan Eletions as </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- An observer team of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) believe the recent
parliamentary elections in Uganda to be fairly smooth and
transparent.
</P>
<P>
The OAU observers were dispatched to the east African country
to monitor the polling on June 27, 1996.
</P>
<P>
An OAU press release said here today that the three-member
team observed campaign rallies, final preparations of the poll
and the conduct of the vote and the count.
</P>
<P>
In some cases, the voting materials reached polling stations
late owing to transport constraints, but the polling staff were
generally competent and voters were aware of the voting
procedures, the release said.
</P>
<P>
The OAU team left Kampala before final results of the
elections were made public, according to the OAU source. 
