<HEADLINE> Pudong's Urban Area Being Expanded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The urbanization of the Pudong New
Area in Shanghai is being accelerated, the Shanghai-based "Business
News" has reported.
</P>
<P>
Its urban area has been expanded from 60 square kilometers to
over 80 square kilometers, forming different functional
urban districts, which are separated by rural areas and linked by
highways.
</P>
<P>
"Such urban districts, which are provided with better
ecological conditions, may avoid noise and air pollution in
cities, and are easily managed," the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The Lujiazui Banking and Trade District has developed 3.13
square kilometers of urban area, and erected more than 100 high
buildings which criss-cross with the streets and roads.
</P>
<P>
The 5.5-square-kilometer Waigaoqiao Bonded Zone has been
fenced, and several buildings built in the first construction
phase have been put into use.
</P>
<P>
Construction of over 200 projects is proceeding well in the
Jinqiao Export-oriented Processing Zone, which has already opened
up eight square kilometers of urban district. The zone, which
looks like an urban garden, is expanding to a 19-square-kilometer
urban area.
</P>
<P>
And the 2.4-square-kilometer Zhangjiang High-tech Zone is home
to about 30 projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
