<HEADLINE> S. Leone Rebels Violate Ceasefire Declaration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FREETOWN, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Rebels of the Revolutionary
United Front (RUF) of Sierra Leone have violated the ceasefire
declaration, defence sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the RUF rebels raided villages near Magburaka
in Tonkolili district in the north in the past few days.
</P>
<P>
"The have been looting rice and other food items and
abducting villagers," the sources said.
</P>
<P>
People in the raided areas are currencly seeking refuge in
displaced camps in Magburaka and Matotoka, a Sierra Leone Red
Cross official said in an interview.
</P>
<P>
In Magburaka, over 8,000 displaced people are now camped at
the Pulbic Works Department displaced camp. They include 87
pregnant women and 714 children under five years old.
</P>
<P>
There are 6,332 displaced people in Matotoka camp.
</P>
<P>
"The displaced camps in Magburaka are suffering from severe
food shortages and medicines," says Mohamed Taqi of the Primary
Health Care Unit in Makeni.
</P>
<P>
Taqui, who returned from the area Thursday, said in a telephone
interview, "the situation is pathetic."
</P>
<P>
A ceasefire agreement was reached between the government and
the RUF rebels three months ago.
