<HEADLINE> Australia Welcomes Indonesia's Ratification of Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Australian Foreign Minister
Alexander Downer today welcomed Indonesia's ratification of a
bilateral security treaty negotiated under the former Labor
government last December.
</P>
<P>
"With the agreement entering into force, another milestone in
relations with Indonesia has been achieved," said Downer, who is
now visiting Vietnam, said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the ratification of the Agreement for Maintaining
Security between the two countries will help to set a very
positive tone for the forthcoming visit to Jakarta by Australian
Prime Minister John Howard.
</P>
<P>
Howard is scheduled to visit Indonesia on August 11-13, his
first official visit to an Asia country since he became the
Australian prime minister last March.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Indonesia and Australia will conduct
regular ministerial consultations on matters of common security
interests to promote security cooperation.
</P>
<P>
A three-page document, signed by Indonesian President Soeharto
and State Secretary Moerdiono, said the agreement entered force on
the date of signing in December.  
</P>
</TEXT>
