<HEADLINE> Iran Attacks USA for Freezing Iranian Assets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani today attacked the United States for freezing Iranian
assets in 1980 and termed it as a "historical criminal act."
</P>
<P>
"We will certainly bring the United States to justice at
international tribunals one day to be condemned (for its act),"
said the 61-year-old president at a large Friday prayer gathering
in Tehran.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. administration seized about 12 billion U.S.dollars
worth of Iranian assets -- some were military purchases -- in the
 United States in 1980 following the take-over of the American
embassy in Tehran by a group of extremist Moslem students.
</P>
<P>
"Nothing can justify such breach of trust and injustice done
by the U.S. against the Iranian people," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He said: "we are now witnessing the disgraceful defeat of
Washington's unilateral sanction and bullying policies against
Iran because even America's closest allies could not tolerate
such intimidations."
</P>
<P>
In the recently concluded G-7 meeting in Lyon, France,
President Bill Clinton failed to convince other member states to
join the unilateral U.S.embargo against Iran.
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani said that if the Americans come to realize the
depth of Iranian people's satisfaction with their officials, they
will never think about confronting Iran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
