<HEADLINE> S.Africa Condemns US Arms Embargo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 5 (Xinhua) -- South African Minister of
Defence Joe Modise has described the United States' continued
arms embargo against South Afria as becoming "irritating".
</P>
<P>
He slammed the US policy while speaking at the release of
ARMSCOR's annual report yesterday in Pretoria.
</P>
<P>
The ARMSCOR company is the country's biggest weapon producer
and exporter.
</P>
<P>
Modise said the arms embargo is affecting the friendship
between the two countries and should not be allowed to continue
since it emanated from the apartheid days.
</P>
<P>
ARMSCOR has once offered to pay a 14.5 million U.S. Dollars in
fine in exchange for the lifting of the embargo, only to be
rejected by the US Justice Department.
</P>
<P>
ARMSCOR handles the acquisition of all equipment including
spare parts for aircraft for the South African defence force.
</P>
<P>
However, the US embargo is making it impossible for the
company to obtain spares. "This meant that other agencies had to
use dubious methods to obtain them," said Modise.
</P>
<P>
South Africa is continuing talks with the United States about
the embargo, but those talks drag "on and on, making it an
irritation". 
</P>
</TEXT>
