<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Fujian Province's Zhangzhou, home to
many overseas Chinese, had a 330 percent increase in the amount of
overseas investment coming in during the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
A city government official says that Zhangzhou signed 95
contracts with foreign companies during that period, involving
1.66 billion US dollars in overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
