<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tibet's Environmental Protection Plans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Tibet Autonomous
Region has developed an ambitious plan to protect the environment
while boosting economic development.
</P>
<P>
The government will have an "environmental target
responsibility system" for the next five years to define
environment protection work at each level of government, according
to the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region's "Southwest Economic
Herald".
</P>
<P>
Environmental protection and agriculture departments will have
ecological agriculture trials, and the region will plant 20,000 ha
of grass and improve 660,000 ha of grass land by the end of the
century.
</P>
<P>
Cultivated land with more than 15 degrees' slope will be
returned to forest and grass, and those with less than 15 degrees
will be changed to terraced fields.
</P>
<P>
Technology transfers will be used in enterprises with severe
pollution problems to ensure that they reach state standards by a
certain deadline. In new projects, environmental protection will
be given priority in the design.
</P>
<P>
By the end of the century, 90 percent of the industrial waste
gas will be treated and 45 percent of solid wastes will be
recycled.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
