<HEADLINE> Pudong Opens Office to Facilitate Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen overseas-funded
enterprises were among the first beneficiaries of an office opened
in the Pudong New Industrial Area to facilitate investment.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises were delighted to find that they were granted
project approval letters and business licenses just ten days after
submitting their applications, as against 60 days previously
needed.
</P>
<P>
The new office is designed to provide a "one-door service" to
speed up domestic and overseas investment in Pudong, Hu Wei,
vice-director of Pudong's Management Committee, said recently.
</P>
<P>
It means investors can get procedures done in the office, which
previously had to go through 15 government departments including
trade, agricultural, planning, taxation, labor, public security,
customs, commodity inspection, quarantine and supply of water,
power and electricity, telecommunications and even cultural
affairs, Hu explained.
</P>
<P>
The office is required to complete examination and approval
within 10 working days of projects involving less than 30 million
US dollars, provided that the projects are under the category of
not being subject to policy restrictions.
</P>
<P>
By 1995, Pudong had attracted 3,501 projects involving a
combined 9.1 billion US dollars of direct investment from 56
countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
This year's goal is to draw 800 projects worth three billion US
dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
