the provincial capital of Guiyang and 13 other towns, flooding
more than 200,000 hectares of farmland, and causing over two
billion yuan of direct economic losses.
</P>
<P>
By July 3, the disasters had reportedly killed 95 people, and
injured more than 600 people, with 21 people missing.
</P>
