<HEADLINE> Major Japanese Aluminum Makers to Post Brisk Earnings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Three leading aluminum producers in
Japan are likely to post an increase in their unconsolidated
pretax profit for fiscal 1996 following rationalization efforts
and brisk sales of electronic parts using aluminum technology,
Kyodo News Service quoted a major business daily as reporting
Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Nihon Keizai Shimbun, Nippon Light Metal
Co. is expected to report an increase in profit thanks to
streamlining efforts and expanding sales of aluminum magnetic
disks.
</P>
<P>
Sumitomo Light Metal Industries Ltd. is likely to see a rise in
sales of air conditioner parts and public works-related business.
</P>
<P>
Showa Aluminum Corp. is likely to reap more profit due to an
increase in sales of heat exchangers for use in automobiles and
electronic components, the paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
