<HEADLINE> hka - Major Japanese Dairy Companies to Report Higher Profits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Three Japanese dairy companies are
likely to report an increase in unconsolidated pretax profit in
fiscal 1996 ending March 31, 1997, Kyodo News Service quoted a a
business daily as saying Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Nihon Keizai Shimbun said the growth will be attributed
mainly to a recovery in sales of ice cream and milk compared with
those in the first half of the previous business year, when
unusual climate irregularities pushed down sales of those products.
</P>
<P>
Among the three dairy companies, Snow Brand Milk Products
Co. is expected to increase its pretax profit by 9 percent to 12
billion yen on sales of 550 billion yen, it said.
</P>
<P>
Meiji Milk Products Co. is likely to post an 11 percent rise to
7.7 billion yen in pretax profit and 432 billion yen in sales, it
said.
</P>
<P>
Morinaga Milk Industry Co. is expected to see an increase in
pretax profit of 3 percent to 7.7 billion yen and a rise in sales
of 2 percent to 415 billion yen, the paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
