<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhejiang's Forest Parks Attracting Millions of Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Forest parks in east China's
Zhejiang Province were visited by a total of 6.5 million overseas
and domestic tourists in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The boom is attributed to the efforts of nearly 10,000 people
who work in the tourism sector of the province, and to the growing
number of special tourist programs and tourist spots.
</P>
<P>
The province now has more than 40 forest parks covering nearly
200,000 hectares. Zhejiang's forest coverage rate ranks first in
China.
</P>
<P>
Its forest parks played host to 8.8 million overseas and
domestic visitors last year. There are more than 60 forest scenic
spots in the capital city of Hangzhou alone.
</P>
<P>
Visitors are attracted by such activities as hunting, boating,
fishing, and camping. 
</P>
</TEXT>
