<HEADLINE> Government Shareholding in Zambian Seed Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The entire 40 percent of the
government shareholding in the Zambia Seed Company Limited
(ZAMSEED ) is on sale for bid, according to an advertisement
which is made public here today.
</P>
<P>
The advertisement from the Privatization Agency says tenders
are invited to bid for the government shareholding in the company
from now on.
</P>
<P>
ZAMSEED was incorporated in 1974 and started its opertions in
1980. It specializes in the production, multiplication, storage
and marketing of a wide range of agricultural, horticultural and
floral seeds.
</P>
<P>
With superior genetic materials, the company has developed a
wide range of seed varieties to meet domestic and regional
customers' requirements. It commands about 70 percent of the
Zambian seed market.
</P>
<P>
The Aambia Privatization Agency is an autonomous agency of the
government of Zambia. Its function is to plan, implement and
control the privatization of state owned enterprises in the
country's economy reforms. 
</P>
