<HEADLINE> Jiangsu's Summer Grain Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Jiangsu Province, one of China's
leading grain producers, reaped summer grain totalling 12 billion
kg this year, 11.9 percent over last year's output, and the second
record harvest in the history of Jiangsu.
</P>
<P>
The harvest is seeing grain increases in 11 cities, including
Yangzhou, which had an increase of 22.6 percent, and Yancheng,
where it was up by 19.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Factors contributing to grain increases include government
protective measures taken to increase sown area for grain
production, and increased government input in agriculture.
</P>
