<HEADLINE> New Expressway Road to Success For Shanxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, July 5 (Xinhua) -- A new expressway in China's Shanxi
province has proved to be a road to success, said vice Governor of
Shanxi Province Xu Jun.
</P>
<P>
He said in Taiyuan today that an international trade fair held
following the opening of the inland province's first express
roadway was fruitful.
</P>
<P>
The 144-kilometer-long expressway links Taiyuan, the provincial
capital, with Jiuguan, a city on the border of Shanxi and
neighboring Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
It is a major passage linking not only Shanxi but also other
middle and western regions with developed eastern regions.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Xu told a press conference that the three-day event in June
led to 16 agreements on joint venture and cooperation projects,
involving direct investments of 34 million US dollars, plus trade
contracts worth 37.5 million US dollars, and five letters of
intent valued at 200 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Business people from 13 countries and regions including the
United States, Australia, Russia, the Republic of Korea, Thailand,
Hongkong and Macao attended the fair.
</P>
<P>
Provincial authorities believe that the expressway will
strongly promote the province's economic cooperation with other
regions and with foreign countries. 
</P>
