<HEADLINE> Township Electronics Industry Spark With Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (xinhua) -- China's township electronics
industry has become a thriving force in the country's electronics
sector.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the Beijing-based "China Township Enterprises
Daily" show that in 1995, the output of township electronics
industry was 70.5 billion yuan, 241 times that of in 1980.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 township companies now send their electronic
products to international markets.
</P>
<P>
According to the newspaper about 60 percent of the companies
are producing spare parts and components for large-scale machinery
and electronic enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation helped township companies promote their
development, it said.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper admitted that there are still some problems
existing in the current township electronics industry, underlining
poor quality in some of the companies.
</P>
<P>
It suggests township enterprises spare no effort in improving
quality of their products, and to raise their competitive ability
on international markets.  
