<HEADLINE> Zimnbabwean Government Functions Decentralised </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Some of the central government
functions to provide housing, health services and education will
be transferred to rural district councils as the Zimbabwean
government implements its decentralisation policy.
</P>
<P>
Announcing on Thursday the progress made in decentralisation,
Local Government, Rural and Urban Development Minister
John Nkomo said the government had put in place clear procedures
and linkages for the implementation of the decentralisation
policy.
</P>
<P>
A 10-member ministerial committee has been set up to oversee
the transfer of duties which goes hand in hand with a five-year
billion dollar capacity building program to adequately equip
rural district councils for the take-over.
</P>
<P>
The levy of taxes will also be transferred to rural councils.
</P>
<P>
John Nkomo said, ''This should not be taken as a strategy of
dumping problems of sector ministries to rural district councils
but an undertaking to promote and strengthen democracy and civic
responsibility as citizens participate in their governance and
development."
</P>
<P>
''That decentralisation should be defined and understood as
the legislated transfer of functions and authority from central
government to local authorities such as rural district councils
on a permanent basis,'' the minsiter stressed. Eenditem

