<HEADLINE> Sino-German Venture Paints Aircraft for International Airlines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-German joint aircraft
maintenance venture has painted a A300-600R aircraft for a Chinese
airline company.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft of China Northern Airlines has already been leased
to Korean Airlines.
</P>
<P>
It is the second time Beijing Aircraft Maintenance and
Engineering Corporation (AMECO), which is China's largest in the
field, has been indirectly involved in aircraft painting for
Korean Airlines. The first one, a Boeing-747, was done four years
ago.
</P>
<P>
"AMECO's painting, which took only nine days to complete, is up
to international standards in terms of work time and quality",
pointed out an aircraft maintenance expert.
</P>
<P>
Sources at Korean Airlines believe that AMECO can win more
projects from international markets with their first-class
service, competitive price and fine maintenance facilities. The
airline itself is considering sending more planes for painting by
AMECO, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
AMECO, jointly funded by Air China and Lufthansa in 1989, has
already undertaken heavy maintenance for three Boeing-747s,
reflecting its high maintenance level.  
</P>
</TEXT>
