<HEADLINE> Beijing College Students Can Watch TV in Dormitories </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Students in Beijing Normal
Institute of Physical Culture can now watch TV in their
dormitories.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 student dormitories in the institute have
installed 14-inch TV sets. All the TV sets are domestically-made
"Peony" color TVs.
</P>
<P>
In the past there were few TV sets in students' dormitories in
colleges and universities.
</P>
<P>
Early this year the local municipal Party committee and
municipal government decided to install closed-circuit TVs in
college students' dormitories, in a bid to enrich cultural
activities in college campuses, and promote ideological and
cultural progress in colleges.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Normal Institute of Physical Culture is the first to
install TV sets in all students' dormitories.
</P>
<P>
Today's "Beijing Daily" quoted a college student as saying that
"This is a good thing for us."
</P>
<P>
The paper said that eight other colleges and universities under
the administration of Beijing are also making preparations to
install TV sets in students' dormitories.
</P>
<P>
Students in most of locally-administered schools of higher
learning are expected to watch TV in dormitories by October.
</P>
</TEXT>
