<HEADLINE> Japanese PM to Visit Central, South America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro
Hashimoto is to go on a 10-day visit to central and south American
countries beginning August 20, government officials said today.
</P>
<P>
The tour will take Hashimoto to Mexico, Brazil, Peru and Chile,
where he is expected to discuss issues to be brought forth to the
Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) forum to be held in the
Philippines in November.
</P>
<P>
Both Mexico and Chile are APEC members.
</P>
<P>
Chile took the place of Argentina after Buenos Aires asked to
be dropped from Hashimoto's itinerary. It will be the first visit
by a Japanese prime minister to Chile in 37 years.
</P>
<P>
In Brazil, the Japanese prime minister is expected to discuss
Brazil's bid to become a permanent member of the U.N. Security
Council, a status that Japan is also seeking, the officials
added. 
