<HEADLINE> Fijitsu Develops Software to Let Kids Use Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 5 (Xinhua) -- World electronics giant Fujitsu
Laboratories Ltd. has developed a software designed to enable
children to enjoy communication through the Internet global
personal computer (PC) network.
</P>
<P>
The software shows on a PC screen a dog, bird, balloon for
other image carrying a message when the computer receives a
message from another PC and then stores the image in an "album",
according to a Kyodo News report.
</P>
<P>
To send a message, an operator opens a scanner by pressing a
"camera shutter" on the screen, picks an image as a messenger and
lets it carry the message.
</P>
<P>
Among other functions, the software enables children, as young
as 6 years old, to process sounds as if to operate a tape
recorder, Fujitsu was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
In order to test the program, PCs will be installed in three
elementary schools in a western prefecture starting Saturday and
connected to computers in Fujitsu Laboratories and prefectural
education centers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
