<HEADLINE> Cambodia Registers Weapons to Fight Crime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia will order its citizens
to re-register their weapons in an effort to stem rising crimes in
the country.
</P>
<P>
Co-Minister of Interior Sar Kheng has signed a directive that
will require all weapons to be re-registered. The measure will go
into effect after the approval of the Ministry of Defense.
</P>
<P>
Existing legislation calls for weapons to be licensed with the
Ministry of Interior, but Interior officials acknowledge that many
weapons are never registered.
</P>
<P>
More than 2,000 illegal weapons were seized in five months this
year.
</P>
<P>
In April and May, foreign embassies reported more than 60
robberies, prompting the Ministry of Interior to form a task force
to help protect the foreign community in the capital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
