<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Colombian Vice President
Humberto de La Calle announced today that he will resign the post
of ambassador to Spain and will return to his country to help
solve the political crisis in his country.
</P>
<P>
Last night, De La Calle met President Ernesto Samper discussing
the situation in Colombia and said that he has different opinions
with Samper on the issue.
</P>
<P>
Colombia has been in crisis since the president was charged
with cover-up, illegal enrichment and electoral fraud. He has been
accused of receiving an estimated 6 million U.S. dollars from the
Cali cocaine cartel in his 1994 election campaign.
</P>
<P>
Some congressmen back Samper and voted to clear the president
of the charges in early June, but some want him to resign.
</P>
<P>
The economy in Colombia has been deteriorating and there is
also a confrontation between the United States and Colombia
because of the dispute over Colombia's anti-drug policy, said the
vice president.
</P>
<P>
"I see a very complicated and anguishing picture in the
country," said de La Calle, while Samper said that the substantial
elements of the crisis had been overcome. 
</P>
