<HEADLINE> Uruguay's Foreign Debt Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Uruguay's net foreign debt
dropped to 2.1 billion U.S. dollars during the first quarter of
this year, 3.7 percent lower than the level at the end of last
year.
</P>
<P>
The Central Bank of Uruguay(CBU) today attributed the drop to
its monetary regulatory measures which reduced the bank's foreign
liabilities.
</P>
<P>
The country's foreign reserves and other assets not residing in
the central bank increased by 43 million U.S. dollars during the
first quarter to 2.726 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The gross foreign debt of the public sector was 4.816 billion
dollars at the end of March. 
</P>
