<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand to Develop 54 Industrial Estates by 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Thailand plans to develop 54
industrial estates nationwide by the year 2000, according to
Industry Ministry sources.
</P>
<P>
Industry Minister Chaiwat Sinasuwong has already ordered the
Industrial Estate Authority of Thailand (IEAT) to speed up
implementation of its industrial estate development plan, as it
has so far developed only 23.
</P>
<P>
Development of industrial estates has been slow because
villagers encroaching on the land to be transferred to IEAT refuse
to leave.
</P>
<P>
The Industry Ministry has asked IEAT to stop concentrating only
on developing state-owned land and begin negotiating with private
land owners who are interested in co-venture.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises in industrial estates enjoy many privileges,
including tax and tariff cuts.
</P>
<P>
Development of industrial estates is also aimed at contributing
to rural development and stemming the flow of labor migration to
big cities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960705.0225 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
