<HEADLINE> Bayer Co. Ltd. Makes Investment in Sichuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The Bayer Company has set up its
first joint venture to produce health foods for animals in China.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture, Bayer Sichuan Animal Health Company, will be
jointly run by the German company and Sichuan Animal
Husbandry-Industry-Commerce Corporation. With a total investment
of 10 million US dollars, the new venture will be based in
Chengdu, capital of Sichuan province.
</P>
<P>
An executive from the German company disclosed that his company
had invested in Sichuan because the province is one of China's key
animal husbandry provinces, and has a mild climate, abundant
rainfall and rich forage grass.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture, in which the German company holds 70 percent
of the shares, will go into production in the first quarter of
next year. It will produce health animal food and some medicines.
</P>
