<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Computer Network Market Thriving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- China's sales volume of computer
network products soared to 133 million US dollars in 1995, up 280
percent from the previous year, "China Electronics News" has
reported.
</P>
<P>
The paper quotes an official with the Ministry of Electronics
Industry as saying that with the rapid development of a series of
information projects, this growth rate of computer network
products will continue into early next century.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that national total sales of computer
products topped 7.4 billion US dollars in 1995, up 14 percent from
the previous year, and 11 times those reported in 1991.
</P>
<P>
The sales of computer hardware reached 2.66 billion US dollars
in 1995, and those of personal computers were 2.03 billion US
dollars, up 62 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
To encourage the rapid development in the domestic computer
network market, the first international computer and network
products trade fair is scheduled to be held between September 18
and 21 this year at the Tianjin International Exhibition Center,
according to the paper.
</P>
<P>
The event will be jointly sponsored by the Ministry of
Electronics Industry, Tianjin Municipality and a US data company.
</P>
</TEXT>
