<HEADLINE> Chinese to Spend More on Clothing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (xinhua) -- Chinese people will spend more on
clothing this year, a new survey made by the State Information
Center and the State Planning Commission shows.
</P>
<P>
Around half of the residents surveyed say they will buy more
clothes this year, the Beijing-based "Market News" reported.
</P>
<P>
The survey also indicates that the demand for clothing by rural
residents is more than in urban areas. Some 57 percent of rural
residents expressed their willingness to buy new clothes, while
the figure for urban people was 46 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the survey indicates that rural residents are now
more attracted to ready-made clothes.
</P>
<P>
On the choice of material, the survey shows that half of the
Chinese people want pure cotton clothes, rather than man-made
materials. 
</P>
