<HEADLINE> Brazilian Jobless Rate Drops in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's unemployment rate
dropped in May for a second month to 5.91 percent, said the
Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics (IBGE).
</P>
<P>
The drop is a reflection of economic improvement during the
second quarter, said the IBGE.
</P>
<P>
The rate was 6.38 percent in March and 6.03 percent in April.
</P>
<P>
The informal labor market had a great role in reducing
unemployment, whose employment rate increased 2.4 percent in May
over April.
</P>
<P>
The service industry had the lowest rate of unemployment, 4.73
percent in April and 4.67 percent in May. In the trade sector, the
jobless rate went down from 6.64 percent in April to 6.41 percent
in May. 
</P>
</TEXT>
