<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing to Rectify Massage Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Beijing has started a crackdown on
pornographic activities and prostitution in massage parlors in the
capital.
</P>
<P>
A notice issued today by Beijing Municipal Public Security
Bureau and Beijing Municipal Administration for Industry and
Commerce, orders all local hotels, restaurants, massage bath
houses and beauty parlors, and other public entertainment centers
to re-register at local administration for industry and commerce
offices before July 30.
</P>
<P>
The new rule excludes medical massage clinics approved by
public health administrative authorities.
</P>
<P>
Today's "Beijing Daily" quoted the notice as saying that
massage by the opposite sex is forbidden in massage services
(excluding massage of the head in beauty parlors and massage of
the feet).
</P>
<P>
Those units which conduct massage services without a license,
or overstep the scope of their activities allowed by their
business licenses, will have licenses cancelled and face severe
punishment by industrial and commercial authorities according to
law.
</P>
<P>
Units engaged in massage services must establish complete rules
and regulations, and impose strict management and education on
their workers.
</P>
<P>
The units are forbidden to employ migrant workers without
identity cards, health cards and job-seeking cards or related
letters of introduction. Violators will be harshly punished by
public security departments and industrial and commercial
authorities according to law.
</P>
<P>
Units which conduct pornographic services and prostitution or
organize, force and introduce prostitution activities under the
shield of massage services, will by harshly dealt with by public
security departments. Those who violate the rules will face
responsibility and criminal charges. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
