<HEADLINE> Russia's Foreign Trade Rises in First Five Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Russia's foreign trade totaled 52.6
billion U.S. dollars in the first five months of this year, an
increase of 10.9 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
During this period, foreign trade surplus increased by 3.2
percent to 13.6 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Of the 52.6 billion dollars, exports accounted for 63 percent
while imports amounted to 37 percent, the Itar-Tass News Agency
quoted the State Customs Committee as saying today.
</P>
<P>
Germany, one of Russia's major trading partners, took the
lion's share, accounting for 8.4 percent of the total, followed by
the United States with 5.7 percent and China with 4.7 percent.
</P>
