<HEADLINE> Beijing Exports More Cellular Telephone Sets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Cellular telephones have become
Beijing's number one export commodity, with over 201,000 exported
in the first five months of this year, according to the Beijing
Municipal Customs Office.
</P>
<P>
An official at the office said that the figure accounted for 16
percent of the city's exports and that it is 34,000 more than the
total for the whole of 1995.
</P>
<P>
Beijing exported 168,028 such sets last year, 274 times the
amount in the previous year, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Beijing currently has two mobile telephone set exporters,
Motorola (China) Company, a Sino-US joint venture, and Ericsson
(China) Electronics Company, a Sino-Swedish joint venture.
</P>
<P>
The Motorola Company exported 186,082 sets and the Ericsson
Company, 15,000 units, from January through May this year.
</P>
<P>
The official said that 200,000 mobile telephone sets, or 99
percent of Beijing's exports of such sets, went to Hong Kong
during the January-May period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
