<DOCNO> XIE19960705.0264 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rains Cause Crop Losses in Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Heavy rains in the last five
days have caused serious losses to rice and coffee crops in Panama.
</P>
<P>
Rice Producers Association reported today that the rains have
beat rice plants down to the ground, making the crop grow
immaturely.
</P>
<P>
The situation is similar for coffee crop. Heavy rains caused
the beans to drop and rot, which could reduce the output by 5
percent.
</P>
<P>
Peasants from Chiriqui Province, the main rice growing region
in Panama, said that rice and coffee yields will be 30 percent and
5 percent lower because of the rains.
</P>
<P>
Bananas, another major crop for the Panamanian economy, is also
affected by the rains, but there is no official estimate of the
damage to banana plantations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
