<HEADLINE> Argentine Exports Post Record in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Argentine exports posted a
record high of 2.4 billion U.S. dollars in May, resulting in a 543
million dollar surplus for the month.
</P>
<P>
The exports figure represents a 5.6 percent increase over that
of the same period last year, according to the lastest report from
the Economic Planning Secretariat of Argentina.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the country's imports rose to 855 million dollars,
an increase of 7.7 percent over that of May in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Argentine exports in the first five months of the year totaled
9.8 billion dollars and imports 8.6 billion dollars, with a
surplus of 475 million dollars, according to the National
Institute of Statistics and Census.
</P>
<P>
The main exports during this period were processed agricultural
and livestock goods, while the main imports were semi-processed
goods and capital goods. 
</P>
