<HEADLINE> Clinton Hails Yeltsin's Re-election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 4 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
today hailed the re-election of Russian President Boris Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
White House officials said that Clinton is expected to hold
telephone talks with Yeltsin on U.S.-Russia relations.
</P>
<P>
"I want to congratulate President Yeltsin on his re-election.
It has a nice ring to it," Clinton said during a stop at Patuxent
Naval Air Station, Maryland, on his way to the White House.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher today also hailed
Yeltsin's re-election in a statement issued in Washington.
</P>
<P>
"Together we now have the opportunity to advance the
considerable progress we have already made with President
Yeltsin's government," Christopher said. 
</P>
