<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment Shanghai On Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai is expected to attract
ten billion US dollars of contractual overseas investment this
year.
</P>
<P>
During the first half of the year the city has already past the
half-way mark, attracting 5.5 billion US dollars of contractual
overseas investment, rising 13.3 percent over the same period in
1995.
</P>
<P>
The majority of local foreign-funded enterprises are operating
industrial projects, helping improve the city's industrial
restructuring to develop local leading items.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investment in local urban areas is focusing on
infrastructure, building commodity housing for domestic buyers,
and homes sold at preferential price.
</P>
<P>
In the suburbs of Shanghai overseas business people are giving
priority to projects of modern agriculture, intensive industry and
urbanization.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Pudong New Area stands as the most attractive
investment spot for foreigners.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has ratified more than 14,000 foreign-funded projects,
involving nearly 40 billion US dollars in contractual overseas
investments, since 1992.
</P>
<P>
More than 9,600 foreign-funded enterprises in Shanghai have
already become operational. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
