<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tibetans in Gongbo'gyamda County Shake off Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Gongbo'gyamda County in southeast
Tibet has climbed out of poverty, reducing the number of the
autonomous region's counties whose residents live under the
state-set poverty level to 17.
</P>
<P>
Surrounded by high mountains and deep water, the county
formerly was one of the poorest areas in the autonomous
region. However, its per capita annual income reached 1,235 yuan
(some 150 U.S.dollars) in 1995. Its population is more than 20,000.
</P>
<P>
The county's total industrial and agricultural output topped 31
million yuan in 1995, an increase of 230 percent over 1990.
</P>
<P>
1995 statistics show that more than 29 percent of households in
the county have an annual income of over 10,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
With the improvement of people's living standards,
Gongbo'gyamda County now attaches more importance to education. In
1995, there were 2,572 students in the county, accounting for 85
percent of its school-age children. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
