<DOCNO> XIE19960705.0271 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tibet Opens Wider to Outside World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The Tibet Autonomous Region has vowed
to open wider to the outside world in a move to accelerate its
economic development.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of the year, 14 provinces and cities have
strengthened their presence in Tibet, combining their talents,
capital and technology with the region's favorable policies and
advantageous resources.
</P>
<P>
"We intend to establish a kind of long-term and cooperative
relationship with developed regions of the country, and their
experiences will promote the rapid development of Tibet's
economy," said a senior official with the autonomous region's
government.
</P>
<P>
Priority has been given to border trade, and Tibet is scheduled
to increase its trade volume with India, Myanmar, and other
countries, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Tibet plans to further improve its investment environment,
enlarge its scope and channels for additional foreign investment,
and raise economic and technological cooperation to a new
level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
