<HEADLINE> France Provides Economic Aid to Haiti </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 4 (Xinhua) - France today signed four agreements of
cooperation with Haiti providing 30 million francs (6 million U.S.
dollars) in aid to the Caribbean island nation, plus a food aid
package amounting to 14 million francs (2.9 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
French minister of cooperation Jacques Godfrain signed the
agreements today in Port-au-Prince at the end of a 24-hour visit
in Haiti to mark the resumption of bilateral cooperation after
Haiti returned to constitutional order on October 15, 1994, said
AFP reports from the Haitian capital.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreements, France will help Haiti revive its
education by providing textbooks and helping organize public
schools, and help it run its financial administration, establish a
public health network and develop pig-breeding trade.
</P>
<P>
France will soon send 5,000 tons of maize and some other food
products worth one million francs to the poverty-striken country.
</P>
</TEXT>
