<HEADLINE> French Cop Officer Sentenced for Drug Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 4 (Xinhua) - Philippe Feval, police superintendent
and former number-two of the Brigade of Repression of Crimes in
Paris, was sentenced today to four years of imprisonment for
organized drug smuggling.
</P>
<P>
Along with Feval, police inspector Thierry Pentz was sentenced
to three years in jail for drug-smuggling and drug-abuse by the
16th correctional chamber of Paris presided by Judge Beatrice de
Beaupuis.
</P>
<P>
Roland Flegat, boss of the Muses restaurant which was used as a
base for drug deals, was given 20 years of jail and 2 million
francs in fines for organized drug smuggling.
</P>
<P>
Mes Patrick Maissoneuve and Philippe Lemaire, attorneys of the
48-year-old former police superintendent, sharply criticized the
sentencing and said they would appeal to a higher court.
</P>
<P>
The three men were immediately locked up after the trial.
</P>
