<HEADLINE> Serb Democratic Party Names Plavsic as Candidate  for Presidency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The Bosnian Serb ruling Democratic
Party today named acting president Biljana Plavsic the candidate
for the Serb president in the upcoming elections.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of the Democratic Party handed the list of
candidates for the September elections to the Organization of
Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE) today, Tanjug news
agency said. OSCE is responsible for the organization and
monitoring of the elections in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
At a session in Serb administrative center Pale late Wednesday,
the Serb Democratic Party main council named current acting
president Plavsic as candidate for Serb president, and Dragoljub
Mirjanic candidate for vice-president, the news agency said.
</P>
<P>
Radovan Karadzic, the Serb leader who resigned as Serb
president last Sunday, decided on Wednesday not to stand as a
candidate of the ruling party in Bosnia's elections although he is
still the head of the party.
</P>
<P>
Heading the party list of candidates for Serb national assembly
is Aleksa Buha, current Serb foreign minister, and Slobodan Bijelic
for the parliament of the union of Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
The candidate for presidency member of the Union of Bosnia is
Momcilo Krajisnik, currently Serb assembly speaker, according to
the list handed to the OSCE today.
</P>
<P>
Elections at municipal, entity and union levels in Bosnia are
scheduled for September 14 in line with the Dayton peace
agreement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
