<HEADLINE> British PM Welcomes Yeltsin's Re-election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 4 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister John Major
today welcomed Boris Yeltsin's victory in the Russian presidential
elections, saying that he looks forward to continuing to work
closely with President Yeltsin and to further steps forward in
relations between Britain and Russia.
</P>
<P>
The Prime Minister said in a statement that he is "delighted by
the successful completion of the presidential elections in Russia
and warmly welcome the re-election of Boris Yeltsin as President".
</P>
<P>
"The result (of the elections) is not only a personal triumph
for President Yeltsin but also a vote for continued political and
economic reform. I believe this will confirm Russia on the path of
stability and rising prosperity," Major added.
</P>
<P>
British foreign Secretary Malcolm Rifkind echoed Major's words,
saying in a statement that "the British government congratulates
President Yeltsin, and welcomes his victory."
</P>
<P>
"President Yeltsin's re-election is an endorsement of his
economic and political reforms, and provides a clear mandate to
press ahead and consolidate the considerable achievements of
recent years. We look forward to continuing our close cooperation
with President Yeltsin in support of reform," Rifkind added.
</P>
